    "recap_headline": "Troy University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HATTIESBURG, Miss.\n- Troy dropped game two of its second Sun Belt series at No. 12 Southern Miss, falling 11-5 as the Golden Eagles evened the series at 1-1.\nWhile the Trojans (10-12, 3-2 SBC) outhit USM (18-5, 2-3 SBC) 12-11, the Golden Eagles capitalized on nine free passes - eight walks and one HBP - by the Troy pitching staff.\nTroy took a brief 2-1 lead in the top of the second, knocking out USM starter Thomas Crabtree after 1.1 innings with a two-RBI single by\nSean Darnell\n. USM grabbed two right back in the bottom of the frame, and the Golden Eagles never trailed again after getting 5.2 innings of relief with four hits, one run and five strikeouts from left-hander Kros Sivley.\nTrojan starter\nDylan Alonso\nwent 3.1 innings, allowing six hits, four runs, three earned runs, no walks and one HPB while striking out three.\nZach Crotchfelt\nfollowed with 2.2 innings in relief, allowing three hits, four runs and four walks while striking out three.\nTroy briefly cut the USM lead to 8-5 in the top of the eighth.\nJosh Pyne\nripped his second double of the game to drive in a run in the seventh, while an RBI double by\nHouston Markham\nand an RBI single by Darnell tacked on two in the eighth.\nBrady Richardson\nworked a clean seventh inning but exited after a one-out walk in the eighth. After two hits and three walks against\nJackson Lucas\nand\nDylan King\n, the Golden Eagles expanded their lead to 11-5 to seal the game.\nNotables\nJosh Pyne\nextended his hitting streak to nine games, going 2-for-4 with two doubles and a walk. He's hitting .410 with seven doubles and one home run during that stretch.\nPyne roped the 66th and 67th doubles of his career, the most among active Division-I players.\nBlake Cavill\nextended his reached base streak to 11 games, going 1-for-4.\nJabe Boroff\nstarted behind the plate for the first time this season. He went 1-for-4, ripping his first double of the season.\nSean Darnell\nwent 2-for-4 out of the nine-hole. He's recorded two hits in three consecutive games.\nQuotable\nHead Coach\nSkylar Meade\n\"They did what we did last night. They were great with two outs. They were able to remain focused. We were unable to stay in a generalized routine. When you take time and you think, it isn't your job to think. We need to get there and go and react. I thought our hitters competed exceptionally well, but late, just not good enough on the hill.\"\nNext Up\nThe series finale between Troy and Southern Miss is set for 1 p.m. at Pete Taylor Park. Senior right-hander\nTommy Egan\nwill start for the Trojans, while the Golden Eagles will trot out redshirt sophomore righty McCarty English.",
